{"actual_usd":0.125445,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":202,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24483,"reply":"\"I don't think you can split them cleanly like that.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the bright square beyond the bakery door, where the well chain gives one soft clink in the noon hush.* \"If Easter is only a symbol, then it's a lovely loaf with no bread in it—warm smell, hollow middle. Christian faith hangs on something God actually did in the world, not just an idea about renewal.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once, thinking it through before I go on.* \"So yes—if the tomb wasn't truly empty, I don't know that you've still got Easter in the Christian sense. You might still have a moving metaphor, and people do live off metaphors for a while. But the faith itself says Christ rose in the flesh. That's the yeast in the whole batch.\"\n\n\"What’s pressing on you here—the history of it, or whether meaning can survive if the fact wobbles?\"","rolling_24h_usd":63.707265,"run_id":"ffc97847-99ab-460f-9425-5ef97bd2e20d"}
